claim.claim-text:
1. A method of using a laryngoscope during a medical procedure on a patient comprising:
providing a laryngoscope handle;
providing a blade for attaching to the handle;
providing a receptacle for temporary storage of the laryngoscope blade, the receptacle having an exterior exposed to the environment around the patient and a normally open mouth leading to an interior area of the receptacle, the receptacle being disposed on a surface;
attaching the blade to the handle to make the laryngoscope operable;
inserting the laryngoscope blade into an oral cavity of the patient;
removing the blade from the oral cavity while maintaining a grip with one hand on the laryngoscope handle;
while still maintaining the grip with the one hand on the laryngoscope handle, inserting the blade through the open mouth into the interior of the receptacle, without touching the laryngoscope with another hand; and
releasing the one hand from the laryngoscope handle so that the handle stays on the exterior of the receptacle while keeping the blade substantially within the interior of the receptacle,
whereby the laryngoscope blade may be stored during the medical procedure in a position isolated from contamination by or contaminating the handle, the surface and the environment around the patient,
